    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "An ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLResource",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " instance used in an argument buffer.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "resource"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "How the compute pass can access data, including ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLResourceUsage/read",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLResourceUsage/write",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " permission.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "For applicable resources, you may be able to prevent the GPU from unnecessarily decompressing color attachments on some devices by setting ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "usage",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " to ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLResourceUsage/read",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "usage"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "mentions",
      "mentions": [
        "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/simplifying-gpu-resource-management-with-residency-sets",
        "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/tracking-the-resource-residency-of-argument-buffers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can make a resource ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "resident",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " (available in GPU memory) for the remaining duration of the compute pass by calling this method. Call the method before encoding function calls that may access the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "resource",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " through an argument buffer. The method ensures the resource is in a format that’s compatible with the kernels that depend on it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "You don’t need to call this method if you bind a resource for compute kernels to access.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The method also informs Metal when to apply hazard tracking for a resource you create with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLHazardTrackingMode/tracked",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For a resource you create with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLHazardTrackingMode/untracked",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", you need to apply an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLFence",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLEvent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to account for potential reading and writing hazards.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can reconfigure an individual resource’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "usage",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " options for subsequent draw calls in the same render pass by calling this method again.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Apps typically call this method for a resource in an argument buffer as a part of their ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "bindless",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " implementation. For more information about argument buffers and bindless implementations, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/improving-cpu-performance-by-using-argument-buffers",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022/10101/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", respectively.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
